README.md
     8Рєњ# Overview
    10Рєњ`once_cell` provides two new cell-like types, `unsync::OnceCell` and `sync::OnceCell`. `OnceCell`
    11Рєњmight store arbitrary non-`Copy` types, can be assigned to at most once and provide direct access
    12Рєњto the stored contents. In a nutshell, API looks *roughly* like this:
    13Рєњ
    14Рєњ```rust
    15Рєњimpl OnceCell<T> {
    16Рєњ    fn new() -> OnceCell<T> { ... }
    17Рєњ    fn set(&self, value: T) -> Result<(), T> { ... }
    18Рєњ    fn get(&self) -> Option<&T> { ... }
    19Рєњ}
    20Рєњ```
    21Рєњ
      РєњРђд
    47Рєњ# Related crates
    49Рєњ* [double-checked-cell](https://github.com/niklasf/double-checked-cell)
    50Рєњ* [lazy-init](https://crates.io/crates/lazy-init)
    51Рєњ* [lazycell](https://crates.io/crates/lazycell)
    52Рєњ* [mitochondria](https://crates.io/crates/mitochondria)
    53Рєњ* [lazy_static](https://crates.io/crates/lazy_static)
    54Рєњ* [async_once_cell](https://crates.io/crates/async_once_cell)
    55Рєњ* [generic_once_cell](https://crates.io/crates/generic_once_cell) (bring your own mutex)
    56Рєњ
    57РєњParts of `once_cell` API are included into `std` [as of Rust 1.70.0](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/105587).
